19:20.400 --> 19:22.400
You're growing up
So damn fast.

19:22.400 --> 19:25.100
And time --
It's hard to explain,

19:25.100 --> 19:29.100
But time just goes
So much faster.

19:34.700 --> 19:37.400
What is it?

19:37.400 --> 19:39.800
Sometimes...

19:39.800 --> 19:43.000
When you talk to me
[exhales]

19:43.000 --> 19:47.000
Sometimes it just doesn't feel
Like you're really here.

19:47.400 --> 19:49.200
What do you mean?

19:49.200 --> 19:53.000
You're always at the hospital,
I think.

19:53.000 --> 19:54.200
But i'm not.

19:54.200 --> 19:55.600
You spend every day

19:55.600 --> 19:58.500
Trying to give strangers
More time to live,

19:58.500 --> 20:02.500
You know, do what they want,
Maybe be with their families.

20:04.200 --> 20:06.700
Right.

20:06.700 --> 20:09.300
It's your time you're
Giving away, you know.

20:09.300 --> 20:11.200
It's your time.

20:23.100 --> 20:26.400
It's the hospital, right?

20:26.400 --> 20:27.600
I have to --

20:27.600 --> 20:29.500
You have to go?

20:29.500 --> 20:31.000
I do.

20:33.400 --> 20:35.000
Can i stay?

20:36.300 --> 20:38.100
You can stay.

20:39.800 --> 20:41.900
Oh, thank you.

20:46.500 --> 20:49.600
????

20:49.600 --> 20:51.300
The minute that this
Starts getting tricky,

20:51.300 --> 20:53.500
I'm gonna take the whole liver
For my patient.

20:53.500 --> 20:54.600
I understand.

20:54.600 --> 20:56.200
I'm not adding
Any more risk.

20:56.200 --> 20:57.100
Fair enough.

20:57.100 --> 20:59.200
It's not because you manipulated
A man of the cloth

20:59.200 --> 21:00.700
To get this opportunity.

21:00.700 --> 21:03.600
Dr. Grant told me if i could
Get any patient to consent --

21:03.600 --> 21:05.600
The reverend grier?
I mean, come on.

21:05.600 --> 21:09.000
You took advantage of this man's
Professional background.

21:09.000 --> 21:11.400
I asked.
He consented.

21:11.400 --> 21:13.100
Please.

21:13.100 --> 21:16.900
Let's get started.
Scalpel?

21:16.900 --> 21:19.000
This has nothing to do with you
Wanting to show dr. Grant

21:19.000 --> 21:20.400
That you know how to do
This procedure?

21:20.400 --> 21:23.200
Dr. Jonas?
Of course i want to try
The procedure. Don't you?

21:23.200 --> 21:25.100
If we get it down, we can save
Twice as many liver patients.

21:25.100 --> 21:26.100
????

21:26.100 --> 21:26.900
Point taken.

21:26.900 --> 21:29.100
So we're good.

21:29.100 --> 21:31.900
Dr. Jonas,
Take a look at this.

21:31.900 --> 21:34.100
Okay. Call it a day.

21:34.100 --> 21:34.900
What is it?

21:34.900 --> 21:38.300
See that? There's a nodule
Of cancer on his liver.

21:38.300 --> 21:40.000
We can't even use
His organs.

21:40.000 --> 21:42.700
This man has cancer.
You got to send him back.

21:57.800 --> 22:00.100
They're getting ready
To take her off the vent

22:00.100 --> 22:01.900
And send her
To the funeral home.

22:12.800 --> 22:14.900
Mr. York?

22:14.900 --> 22:18.200
If you're here for her organs,
You better walk away.

22:18.200 --> 22:19.800
I'm not.

22:23.000 --> 22:24.900
Are you one
Of her doctors?

22:24.900 --> 22:28.400
No.

22:28.400 --> 22:30.700
Who are you?

22:30.700 --> 22:33.200
I'm a surgeon,

22:33.200 --> 22:36.200
And i'm here because --

22:36.200 --> 22:38.700
Because i know
What happened.

22:42.100 --> 22:45.600
And i'm a father, too.

22:45.600 --> 22:48.400
And i'm so sorry.

22:51.400 --> 22:54.200
Mr. York...

22:54.200 --> 22:56.100
I'm just so sorry.

23:10.100 --> 23:11.800
I'm sorry, teddy.

23:15.100 --> 23:17.500
They can't use
The sheriff's organs.

23:17.500 --> 23:20.300
I know.

23:20.300 --> 23:22.400
I should just quit.

23:22.400 --> 23:23.300
Teddy --

23:23.300 --> 23:27.300
I can't make any
Of these things work.

23:28.400 --> 23:30.100
It's not your fault.

23:30.100 --> 23:33.100
The family
Goes through all this...

23:33.100 --> 23:35.900
Accepts his death...

23:35.900 --> 23:37.600
Agrees to donate...

23:37.600 --> 23:43.000
And it doesn't work out.

23:43.000 --> 23:45.700
Teddy, there was
A cancerous mass.

23:45.700 --> 23:48.100
Nothing showed up on our tests.
It happens.

23:48.100 --> 23:52.000
But to get
All the way there...

23:52.000 --> 23:54.500
And to have to
Tell them again.

23:56.200 --> 23:59.600
It's the worst part
Of our job.

23:59.600 --> 24:01.900
It's a second death.

24:01.900 --> 24:05.300
Isn't there some comfort
In knowing if it was cancer,

24:05.300 --> 24:09.300
He might've avoided,
You know...

24:10.100 --> 24:11.800
Later?

24:11.800 --> 24:14.200
There's no comfort.

24:15.700 --> 24:17.600
Their dad got shot
In the head,

24:17.600 --> 24:21.400
And now they can't even donate
His organs.

24:21.400 --> 24:23.500
They're not comforted.

24:23.500 --> 24:25.800
They're not happy.

24:29.400 --> 24:31.700
Why don't you
Take a moment?

24:31.700 --> 24:35.700
I know how this sounds...

24:35.900 --> 24:40.200
But i finally,
Finally got a consent.

24:40.200 --> 24:42.800
From a cop's wife,
No less.

24:45.000 --> 24:47.300
????

24:53.700 --> 24:55.300
Ali york

24:55.900 --> 24:58.200
Multiple orga donor

25:23.000 --> 25:24.600
Kate: an operating room
Just opened up.

25:24.600 --> 25:25.900
If you could just stay
With the donners

25:25.900 --> 25:29.600
While i offer the organs.

25:29.600 --> 25:30.600
I'd rather not.

25:30.600 --> 25:33.300
Temple, stay with the donners.
Make sure he's stable.

25:33.300 --> 25:34.300
But...

25:34.900 --> 25:37.400
This is a potential
Eight-organ donor.

25:37.400 --> 25:40.600
Can you do this, or should i
Bring someone else in?

25:43.000 --> 25:45.600
I can do it.

25:45.600 --> 25:50.300
Temple, you just need to
Remember why we're doing this,

25:50.300 --> 25:53.200
How many people are waiting.

25:53.200 --> 25:54.900
You're right.

25:57.500 --> 25:59.000
Thank you.

26:08.600 --> 26:09.800
Hey.
Hey.

26:09.800 --> 26:11.100
I was looking for you.

26:11.100 --> 26:13.000
How you doing?

26:13.000 --> 26:16.200
It's been...
It's been a day.

26:16.200 --> 26:17.600
Are you all right?

26:17.600 --> 26:21.000
Of all the days to be training
A new coordinator.

26:21.000 --> 26:23.300
Anyway, i have an organ
For you.
Oh, great.

26:23.300 --> 26:29.800
A liver for a patient
Named mitchell stubbs.

26:30.200 --> 26:31.200
Mr. Stubbs?
Mm-hmm.

26:31.200 --> 26:33.500
His kidney failure put him
At the top of our list.

26:39.800 --> 26:40.900
Right.

26:41.900 --> 26:43.400
Is there a problem?

26:43.400 --> 26:44.600
No.

26:44.600 --> 26:48.600
Should i send
The liver on?
No. No problem.

26:49.400 --> 26:51.600
The operating room
Has been arranged.

26:51.600 --> 26:53.000
Okay.
I'll be down in a few minutes.

26:53.000 --> 26:54.300
Great.

27:00.200 --> 27:03.700
Mr. Stubbs,
We have some good news.

27:03.700 --> 27:05.800
We've located an organ
For you.

27:05.800 --> 27:07.700
Is it the donner kid?

27:07.700 --> 27:10.000
We can't disclose the name
Of the donors.

27:10.000 --> 27:13.500
It's got to be
The donner kid.

27:13.500 --> 27:16.600
Mr. Stubbs,
Can you focus for a moment?

27:18.600 --> 27:20.100
So, a liver
Has become available,

27:20.100 --> 27:23.000
And you're now first
On the recipient list...

27:23.000 --> 27:23.600
Okay.

27:23.600 --> 27:25.900
...which means we need to
Ask your permission

27:25.900 --> 27:27.900
To share the organ.

27:27.900 --> 27:29.200
What?

27:29.200 --> 27:31.200
You were brought to st. Jude's
Because another recipient

27:31.200 --> 27:33.600
Was kind enough to share
His donated liver with you,

27:33.600 --> 27:37.000
So we need to make sure you're
Comfortable doing the same.

27:37.000 --> 27:38.600
I can have my own?

27:38.600 --> 27:40.500
You can.

27:40.500 --> 27:43.200
Then i want my own.

27:43.200 --> 27:44.200
Mr. Stubbs --

27:44.200 --> 27:47.200
If it's mine,
I want it.

27:58.500 --> 28:00.500
Hey.
So we're good, right?

28:02.500 --> 28:03.800
What?

28:05.900 --> 28:07.500
He -- he won't.

28:07.500 --> 28:09.200
He won't what?

28:09.200 --> 28:11.200
He won't share the liver.

28:11.200 --> 28:14.600
Oh, come on.

28:14.600 --> 28:16.800
Reverend grier was gonna
Give him half,

28:16.800 --> 28:19.300
And now he gets nothing?

28:19.300 --> 28:20.300
I'm sorry.

28:20.300 --> 28:24.300
But mr. Stubbs
Wouldn't even be here.

28:24.300 --> 28:27.900
Vancouver, you had to go
Take advantage, didn't you?

28:27.900 --> 28:29.400
Dr. Jonas --
Look, you know what?

28:29.400 --> 28:32.600
I just wanted one thing
In my life to be clear.

28:32.600 --> 28:34.000
This was
A simple situation

28:34.000 --> 28:38.000
Where we could've done some good
For a good person.

28:38.300 --> 28:42.100
Dr. Jonas, your operating room
Is ready.

28:48.500 --> 28:51.400
Oh ???

29:00.800 --> 29:02.100
Duane donner

29:02.500 --> 29:05.100
Multiple organ donor

29:24.400 --> 29:25.800
How'd it go?

29:25.800 --> 29:27.400
We got 'em all.

29:27.400 --> 29:28.200
They all look good?

29:28.200 --> 29:31.000
All eight.
Perfect condition.

29:31.000 --> 29:33.400
Did you take thea home?

29:33.400 --> 29:37.400
No. I took her out
To pinehurst lake.

29:38.100 --> 29:39.400
What?

29:39.400 --> 29:41.200
I took her out there,
I made sure she was okay,

29:41.200 --> 29:43.400
And then i left her
With her friends.

29:44.900 --> 29:48.700
We do our best, katie,
But we're not always deliberate.

29:48.700 --> 29:50.600
You know, we practice
Benign neglect,

29:50.600 --> 29:52.600
And we don't want
To pay the price for it.

29:52.600 --> 29:54.000
I don't think
We're neglecting her.

29:54.000 --> 29:56.000
I'm not trying to undermine
Your decisions.

29:56.000 --> 29:58.800
I just mean that --

29:58.800 --> 30:00.600
I don't know.

30:01.600 --> 30:04.600
When i saw
That dead girl today,

30:04.600 --> 30:09.700
I just thought, "it's such
A beautiful day outside."

30:13.100 --> 30:16.200
It was just
Such a beautiful day.

30:24.700 --> 30:26.900
So, you'll get a letter from me
In a few days

30:26.900 --> 30:29.700
With some of the details --
Where your son's organs ended up

30:29.700 --> 30:33.200
And some broad information
About the recipients.

30:33.200 --> 30:35.200
I could meet them?

30:35.200 --> 30:39.200
In time, if you wanted to,
And if they agree.

30:39.400 --> 30:41.900
They'd never agree,
Not to meet me.

30:41.900 --> 30:43.800
Mrs. Donner,
You never know.

30:43.800 --> 30:46.500
People aren't always
What you expect.

30:46.500 --> 30:47.600
Well...

30:49.200 --> 30:50.600
Hold back.

30:50.800 --> 30:52.600
Sorry, folks,
Can't go in.

30:52.600 --> 30:56.600
We can keep you here
For a while, if you'd like.

30:57.000 --> 30:58.900
They want to talk to me.

30:58.900 --> 31:02.900
They want to know why he did
What he did.

31:03.600 --> 31:05.500
I'm sure they do.

31:06.600 --> 31:09.100
Maybe the answer is me.

31:09.100 --> 31:14.400
Maybe this happened because
Of the things i didn't do.

31:15.200 --> 31:17.800
But you couldn't
Have known.

31:17.800 --> 31:19.700
You couldn't have known.

31:25.900 --> 31:27.400
Yeah.

31:51.800 --> 31:53.200
You're angry with me?

31:53.200 --> 31:54.600
I am.

31:57.000 --> 31:59.600
I'm sorry if i --

31:59.600 --> 32:02.100
You walked away
From our agreement.

32:02.100 --> 32:02.700
I did.

32:02.700 --> 32:05.100
And manipulated your father
Into getting what you wanted.

32:05.100 --> 32:06.000
I didn't.

32:06.000 --> 32:08.200
You did.

32:10.700 --> 32:14.700
When you are with me,
It's my rules.

32:14.800 --> 32:18.100
You don't go to your father
And ask for them to be changed.

32:18.100 --> 32:20.400
It was fine, mom.
I had so much fun and --

32:20.400 --> 32:21.500
Fun?

32:21.500 --> 32:23.900
You had fun.

32:23.900 --> 32:25.700
Well, that's terrific,
Thea.

32:25.700 --> 32:28.400
You lied to me, went somewhere
You weren't supposed to go,

32:28.400 --> 32:31.300
So if that's your idea
Of fun --

32:31.300 --> 32:33.100
Temple: kate?

32:33.600 --> 32:37.100
Are we done now, or do we still
Have paperwork to file?

32:37.100 --> 32:41.100
We've got about an hour
Of charting left to do at least.

32:41.200 --> 32:43.900
Why don't you wait here?
I'll bring it up.

33:21.800 --> 33:24.600
Knock, knock.

33:24.600 --> 33:27.700
I asked dad
To drop me off here.

33:28.800 --> 33:32.600
I was wondering
If you wanted some help.

33:32.600 --> 33:36.600
I could do some of these
For you, if you want.

33:49.700 --> 33:53.700
So many people.

33:54.000 --> 33:55.500
Mm-hmm.

33:57.300 --> 34:00.600
It's sad.

34:00.600 --> 34:03.000
Sometimes.

34:03.000 --> 34:05.400
I meant for you and dad.

34:07.000 --> 34:09.500
It's got to be sad.

34:20.000 --> 34:23.000
So it was fun?

34:23.000 --> 34:25.000
What?

34:25.000 --> 34:27.600
At the lake?

34:28.000 --> 34:30.600
Yeah.

34:31.400 --> 34:33.400
Were the boys cute?

34:35.900 --> 34:38.400
Hmm...yeah.

34:40.699 --> 34:42.800
And they were nice to you?

34:42.800 --> 34:46.400
Yes, mom,
They were nice to me.

34:48.400 --> 34:49.900
I'm glad.

34:52.000 --> 34:53.699
I'm glad.

35:20.900 --> 35:24.700
Looks like a pretty day.

35:24.700 --> 35:26.600
I haven't been out yet.

35:26.600 --> 35:29.300
You stayed here the whole night
Finishing those cards?

35:29.300 --> 35:30.400
Mm-hmm.

35:33.500 --> 35:35.300
Temple...

35:38.200 --> 35:43.400
Yesterday i -- i hope
I didn't push you too hard.

35:47.100 --> 35:48.600
Did i?

35:51.600 --> 35:52.500
Didn't you feel

35:52.500 --> 35:57.800
That maybe giving
The killer's organs was --

35:57.800 --> 36:04.300
I don't know --
In a way morally wrong?

36:05.100 --> 36:07.600
Morally?

36:08.100 --> 36:14.500
I stood there, and i held
That man's hand, okay?

36:17.200 --> 36:20.500
I saw what he did to that girl
And that cop.

36:22.600 --> 36:25.000
And i held his hand.

36:27.200 --> 36:29.200
Temple...

36:29.600 --> 36:32.900
What he did
Was morally wrong.

36:34.900 --> 36:37.200
But his organs saving
Other people's lives

36:37.200 --> 36:40.700
Was probably the only just thing
To come out of that situation.

36:49.900 --> 36:53.400
I don't know
If i can do this.

36:55.500 --> 36:59.500
Well, i promise you
It gets easier.

37:00.200 --> 37:02.600
Is that true,

37:02.600 --> 37:06.200
Or do you just get used to
How hard it is?

37:15.800 --> 37:18.200
Come on.

37:18.200 --> 37:22.200
Why don't you help me take
These cards to the park?

37:23.400 --> 37:26.300
You'll like this.

37:33.700 --> 37:36.000
Reverend grier?

37:37.400 --> 37:39.700
Reverend grier?

37:46.300 --> 37:48.100
Hey.

37:48.100 --> 37:50.100
Are you coming
To this thing?

37:50.100 --> 37:53.600
No, i'm gonna stay here
In case an organ comes in.

37:55.700 --> 37:58.600
Listen, i wasn't trying
To push mr. Stubbs up the list.

37:58.600 --> 38:02.100
I just -- i was just trying
To relieve his pain.

38:02.100 --> 38:04.700
Well, you did what you did,
Dr. Griffith.

38:04.700 --> 38:07.700
I am not here to tell you
You did the wrong thing.

38:07.700 --> 38:09.000
Yeah, but the result --

38:09.000 --> 38:10.100
Listen.

38:10.100 --> 38:14.100
????

38:36.100 --> 38:37.900
We thought
We scared you off.

38:37.900 --> 38:39.200
Almost.
[ chuckles ]

38:39.800 --> 38:42.600
Is that
Duane donner's balloon?

38:42.600 --> 38:44.400
It is.

38:44.900 --> 38:48.700
It's the right thing to do,
Remembering him despite --

38:48.700 --> 38:51.400
I know.

38:51.400 --> 38:53.200
Do you want me
To take it?

38:55.500 --> 38:57.000
I've got it.

38:59.900 --> 39:02.400
This is for you.

39:06.200 --> 39:07.700
[ chuckles ]
Bradley rogers.

39:07.700 --> 39:10.700
Mm-hmm.
You did everything you could.

39:10.700 --> 39:12.400
It just didn't
Go our way.

39:12.400 --> 39:14.800
Thanks.

39:14.800 --> 39:17.300
And you got the consent.

39:17.300 --> 39:18.800
You're right.

39:18.800 --> 39:22.200
Mm-hmm, so let it go.

39:23.500 --> 39:28.400
* ah *

39:29.900 --> 39:33.900
* hold me, love *

39:34.300 --> 39:38.100
* i can't sleep again *

39:38.100 --> 39:42.100
* i have to kiss your lips *

39:42.200 --> 39:48.600
* i want to lay here
Next to him, love *

39:50.000 --> 39:53.900
* i remember *

39:53.900 --> 39:57.800
* walking in the rain *

39:57.800 --> 40:01.800
* rain was falling on my hands *

40:01.900 --> 40:07.800
* i don't want to live
Through that again, no *

40:10.200 --> 40:13.100
* outside *

40:13.100 --> 40:17.700
* it hardly gets dark now *

40:17.700 --> 40:21.300
* lovers walking
In the park now *

40:21.300 --> 40:23.500
* children singing songs *

40:23.500 --> 40:28.400
* of when they'll make
All their dreams come true *

40:29.100 --> 40:30.700
My daughter --

40:30.700 --> 40:33.000
She's 14 years old now,

40:33.000 --> 40:36.700
And i can't stop thinking of her
As 6, you know?

40:38.200 --> 40:41.500
Seems like
She was just that age.

40:41.500 --> 40:44.000
Everything i said
Was funny.

40:44.000 --> 40:47.000
Always on my shoulders.

40:47.000 --> 40:51.000
Always wanted me
To play with her.

40:51.000 --> 40:54.300
She's not 6 anymore.

40:54.300 --> 40:58.000
And that's good.

40:58.000 --> 41:00.100
I kind of miss that time,
You know?

41:00.100 --> 41:02.500
Talking to yourself?

41:02.500 --> 41:05.800
Yeah.

41:05.800 --> 41:07.500
Listen, if i did the wrong thing
Yesterday --

41:07.500 --> 41:11.500
Thea tells me you tied the
Rope swing and went swimming.

41:11.600 --> 41:14.700
Yeah.

41:14.700 --> 41:16.800
Good for you.

41:16.800 --> 41:18.400
You think?

41:18.400 --> 41:20.800
How long has it been
Since you took a day off?

41:22.600 --> 41:25.300
22 years.

41:25.300 --> 41:27.600
Good for you.

41:27.600 --> 41:29.600
There's
So many people here.

41:29.600 --> 41:32.000
All those cards
And balloons.

41:32.000 --> 41:35.300
Yeah.

41:35.300 --> 41:41.500
* i would see you walking
In your coat, oh *

41:42.200 --> 41:45.600
You knew all
Of them, huh?

41:45.600 --> 41:48.400
Most of them.

41:48.400 --> 41:51.000
There are a lot.

41:51.000 --> 41:55.000
Not nearly enough.

41:55.100 --> 41:56.800
Who is your balloon for,
Dad?

41:56.800 --> 41:58.900
It's just a balloon.

42:01.600 --> 42:03.600
Where's yours?

42:05.600 --> 42:07.100
I don't have one.

42:07.100 --> 42:08.500
Why not?

42:08.500 --> 42:12.100
They're all your mother's,
Thea.

42:12.100 --> 42:13.200
Really?

42:15.600 --> 42:19.200
Guess i do kind of think of them
As all my own.

42:21.600 --> 42:23.400
But you go ahead,
Sweetie.

42:26.500 --> 42:29.300
Go ahead
